{"key":"processedPost-12762761","value":{"id":12762761,"first":12760114,"last":12762761,"when":1276876887,"utime":"06/18/10 07:01 PM","content":"Get hydrated lime.&nbsp; You can find it easily with an internet search, or go to your local feed store.&nbsp; Farmers use it all the time to neutralize the stink from dead animals and manure, etc. I get 50 pound bags of hydrated lime locally for $6.<br /><br />You can also use ground limestone.&nbsp; Don't use any lime from dolomite rock formations.&nbsp; The MG will ruin the mycelium.<br />RR","title":"Re: lime & straw","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}